03927nam a22005175i 9780520931879DE-B159720200623100627.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||200623t20202005cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805209318797 a10.1525/97805209318792doi  a(DE-B1597)563055  a(OCoLC)1163878945  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 4aBP182b.C66 2005eb 7aREL0370002bisacsh04a297.7/22221 aCook, David, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aUnderstanding Jihad /cDavid Cook. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2020] 4cÂ©2005  a1 online resource (269 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tACKNOWLEDGMENTS -- tINTRODUCTION -- t1. Qur'an and Conquest -- t2. The "Greater Jihad" and the "Lesser Jihad" -- t3. The Crystallization of Jihad Theory: Crusade and Counter-Crusade -- t4. Jihad during the Nineteenth Century: Renewal and Resistance -- t5. Radical Islam and Contemporary Jihad Theory -- t6. Globalist Radical Islam and Martyrdom Operations -- tAfterword -- tAppendix: Some Translated Documents -- tTimeline -- tGlossary -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex 0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aJihad is one of the most loaded and misunderstood terms in the news today. Contrary to popular understanding, the term does not mean "holy war." Nor does it simply refer to the inner spiritual struggle. This book, judiciously balanced, accessibly written, and highly relevant to today's events, unravels the tangled historical, intellectual, and political meanings of jihad. Looking closely at a range of sources from sacred Islamic texts to modern interpretations, Understanding Jihad opens a critically important perspective on the role of Islam in the contemporary world. As David Cook traces the practical and theoretical meanings of jihad, he cites from scriptural, legal, and newly translated texts to give readers a taste of the often ambiguous information that is used to construct Islamic doctrine. He looks closely at the life and teaching of the Prophet Muhammad and at the ramifications of the great Islamic conquests in 634 to 732 A.D. He sheds light on legal developments relevant to fighting and warfare, and places the internal, spiritual jihad within the larger context of Islamic religion. He describes some of the conflicts that occur in radical groups and shows how the more mainstream supporters of these groups have come to understand and justify violence. He has also included a special appendix of relevant documents including materials related to the September 11 attacks and published manifestoes issued by Osama bin Laden and Palestinian suicide-martyrs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aIslamy21st century. 0aIslamic fundamentalism. 0aJihad. 0aWarxReligious aspectsxIslam. 7aRELIGION / Islam / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520931879423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520931879.jpg  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles